O $15.99 Shop All Browse By We curate each product, selecting only the finest available in the US Subscriptions & Boxes Curated selections of tins at a very special price Shop Boxes Fish The classics: tuna, sardines, anchovies, and more Shop Fish Seafood The finest shellfish, octopus and squid Shop Seafood Pâté, Sauces and More Not everything in life is seafood. Pick from our pates, sauces and snacks Shop More Our Story We’re four Spanish friends who met over a decade ago in New York City — brought together by a shared love of great food, good company, and the rituals that make everyday moments special. One ritual we missed most from back home? Conservas — the cherished Spanish tradition of gathering with friends to enjoy tins of exceptional seafood, a splash of vermouth, and unhurried conversation. It’s a celebration of flavor, heritage, and connection. That’s the spirit behind Lata — which means tin in Spanish. To bring this experience stateside, we’ve built close relationships with producers across Spain and Portugal — many of them small, family-run conservas houses that use traditional methods to ensure unmatched freshness, texture, and sustainability. We founded Lata to share these incredible tins — and the timeless ritual behind them — with more people. One day, we hope to open a vermouth bar to bring this experience to life in person. Until then, we invite you to join us — tin by tin. Read Our Blog Our Newest Tins New Add to Cart Lata Picante Box $49.99 Sold Out Sold Out Lata Tuna Pâté with Padrón Peppers Sold Out Add to Cart Lata Spicy Mussel Pâté $8.99 Add to Cart Lata Squid in Ink Pâté $9.99 Sold Out Sold Out Lata Codfish Pâté with Raisins and Caramelized Onions Sold Out Add to Cart Lata Small Sardines in Olive Oil with Padrón Peppers $11.99 What's New? Get Inspired by Our Recipes Pasta Con Le Sarde Curry Tuna Salad with Celery, Cashews, and Lime Sardine Banh Mi Midnight Rice with Stuffed Squid in Ink Why Lata We are a group of friends from Spain living in the United states that share a passion for canned food and miss it so much that decided to source the best products from Spain. Sourced with Care We work directly with small producers across Spain and Portugal — many of them family-run — who still use traditional methods to preserve seafood at peak freshness and texture. Our tins reflect generations of heritage and craft. Curated by Us We taste every tin and only select the very best. You won’t find a crowded marketplace here — just a tight, rotating collection of standouts we personally love and believe in. Rooted in Ritual Behind every tin is a story, a culture, and a moment meant to be savored. Whether you’re new to conservas or a lifelong fan, we hope Lata brings a little joy and nostalgia to your table. Our Latest Updates Bem Amanhado: A Different Kind of Conserva Last year, on a flight from Valencia to New York, I had a layover in Lisbon. Whenever I can, I try to stay a few hour... The Best Canned Sardines: 6 Exceptional Brands to Try in 2025 From buttery, melt-in-your-mouth fillets to bold, briny bites perfect for tapas, choosing the best canned sardines ... A Year of Gratitude and Growth: Thank You from Us As four Spaniards living in New York, our journey with Lata has been a dream come true. When we started, we hoped to ... Stay Updated -- Currency USD $ AED د.إ AFN ؋ ALL L AMD դր. ANG ƒ AUD $ AWG ƒ AZN ₼ BAM КМ BBD $ BDT ৳ BIF Fr BND $ BOB Bs. BSD $ BWP P BZD $ CAD $ CDF Fr CHF CHF CNY ¥ CRC ₡ CVE $ CZK Kč DJF Fdj DKK kr. DOP $ DZD د.ج EGP ج.م ETB Br EUR € FJD $ FKP £ GBP £ GMD D GNF Fr GTQ Q GYD $ HKD $ HNL L HUF Ft IDR Rp ILS ₪ INR ₹ ISK kr JMD $ JPY ¥ KES KSh KGS som KHR ៛ KMF Fr KRW ₩ KYD $ KZT ₸ LAK ₭ LBP ل.ل LKR ₨ MAD د.م. MDL L MKD ден MMK K MNT ₮ MOP P MUR ₨ MVR MVR MWK MK MYR RM NGN ₦ NIO C$ NPR Rs. NZD $ PEN S/ PGK K PHP ₱ PKR ₨ PLN zł PYG ₲ QAR ر.ق RON Lei RSD РСД RWF FRw SAR ر.س SBD $ SEK kr SGD $ SHP £ SLL Le STD Db THB ฿ TJS ЅМ TOP T$ TTD $ TWD $ TZS Sh UAH ₴ UGX USh USD $ UYU $U UZS so'm VND ₫ VUV Vt WST T XAF CFA XCD $ XOF Fr XPF Fr YER ﷼ Amazon American Express Apple Pay Google Pay Mastercard PayPal Shop Pay Visa -- Account Sign In Register Sign Up For Newsletter About Contact Us About Us FAQ Instagram Blog Recipes News Guides Work With Us Wholesale Corporate Gifting Brand Ambassador Policies Shipping Return & Refund Terms & Conditions Conditions of Use Amazon American Express Apple Pay Google Pay Mastercard PayPal Shop Pay Visa Lata &copy; 2026 Close (esc) Not sure where to start? Join our Discovery Box subscription and receive a specially curated selection of products every month at an even more unbeatable price. Learn More Age verification By clicking enter you are verifying that you are old enough to consume alcohol. Enter Search Search Main menu Shop All Subscriptions and Boxes Brands About Us Wholesale Blog -- Shopping Cart Your cart is currently empty. Shop now &nbsp &nbsp &nbspTruveta | myResearchPath Skip to main content Utility Menu back to myRESEARCHhome Home Open Menu Home About Updates Feedback Log in Search Truveta Jump to this section of the page: Top of Page Associated Topics Truveta aggregates electronic health record data from 30+ health systems and makes a de-identified version available to users for research and analytics. The Truveta dataset includes full patient medical records linked across health systems (including clinical notes, images, and genomics), augmented with social determinants of health, mortality, pharmacy (dispensing), and open claims data. Structured data domains within the Truveta system include demographics, diagnoses, procedures, medications, laboratory results, immunizations, genomic markers, device information and care setting. Unstructured data domains include notes, imaging reports, flowsheets and pathology reports. SDOH, claims and mortality data are linked from LexisNexis, while pharmacy data is sourced from Surescripts. Truveta receives a daily data feed from contributing health systems, where the data are cleaned and normalized before being de-identified. The dataset represents more than 100M patients, with patient and encounter level data from 20,000+ hospitals and clinics, covering 50 states. Truveta access Use of Truveta data incurs fees based on the amount of data needed, computational usage for analysis, and storage amount needed for analytic data sets. Access by Duke researchers to Truveta data is determined by funding mechanism; i.e. Internal or External funding: Researchers requesting access to Truveta planning to utilize INTERNAL Funding (ex. Discretionary or Departmental funds) Access to Truveta data by researchers planning to use INTERNAL funding is managed by the Department of Population Health DataShare. To request access to Truveta complete this REDCap intake survey . Only one survey is needed per project. Team members who are authorized to work on a project in Truveta Studio will need to log in here using their Duke credentials (in the netID@duke.edu format) before account provisioning can occur. Truveta fees will be invoiced monthly on a per project basis. A small monthly administrative fee is charged to cover invoice processing for each project. The following resources are available for researchers with additional questions about Truveta data: Truveta monthly training sessions Truveta monthly office hours A Duke Box folder containing slides/recordings from the March onboarding training, as well as a MS Team for Duke Truveta users to share questions, tidbits, etc. Requests to receive invitations to the monthly training sessions, monthly office hours, and/or the Duke Box folder and MS Duke Truveta users team should email pophealthdatashare@dm.duke.edu Researchers requesting access to Truveta planning to utilize EXTERNAL funding (i.e. Sponsor or Grant funds): Access to Truveta by researchers planning to use EXTERNAL funding should contact Truveta directly ( https://www.truveta.com/research/ ) for information on budgeting and potential costs associated with data access/analysis/storage. Home Back to Top myRESEARCHpath is maintained in partnership by the Duke Office of Research Initiatives and participating research support offices across the institution. Footer menu About Feedback HomeHealthcare Data, Intelligence, and Evidence | Truveta Data Truveta Data A complete, living view of patient care Explore Truveta Data Capabilities Representative, complete, and real-time Clinical notes Genomics Images Mother-child Regulatory grade data Truveta Language Model Live Link Oncology Evidence Build trust through rigorous analytics and expertise Trusted research environment Evidence Services Intelligence Truveta Intelligence Answers in minutes, not months Explore Truveta Intelligence Capabilities Ask what matters now Ask Evidence Verify the methodology behind the results Verify Customers Truveta customers Trusted by leading life science, public health, and healthcare organizations Who we serve Pharmaceutical Medical device Healthcare Public Health Research About Saving Lives with Data Built with and owned by US health systems to improve patient care Resources Members Leadership News Events & webinars Careers Contact us Sign in  Close Saving Lives with Data Real-time intelligence from real-world data Answers can't wait Get started Get started 7 Truveta Data The most complete, real-time view of US healthcare 1 in 3 Americans All care settings Updated daily 10+ years of history 130M+ Patients and growing Longitudinally linked: EHR Closed claims Devices Images SDOH Mother-child Multiomics Mortality Explore Truveta Data Explore Truveta Data Truveta Intelligence Answers in minutes, not months Explore Truveta Intelligence Explore Truveta Intelligence Truveta Evidence Confidence through rigorous analytics and expertise Trusted research environment Immediately access Truveta Data and execute full research studies Dynamically refine cohorts with reusable, clinically precise definitions Produce audit-ready evidence aligned to regul